1.text: Read the poem and answer the questions. Flying I saw the moon, One windy night, Flying so fast— All silvery white— Over the sky Like a toy balloon Loose from its string— A runaway moon. The frosty stars Went racing past, Chasing her on Ever so fast. Then everyone said, "It's the clouds that fly, And the stars and moon Stand still in the sky." But I don't mind— I saw the moon Sailing away Like a toy Balloon. J. M. Westrup 1. What is the poem about? a) the sky b) the moon c) the toy balloon 2. What did the moon look like? a) a toy balloon b) a star c) a string
